This paper discusses bibliometric indicators, which are commonly used in the field of computer science to evaluate the impact of research publications. The paper specifically focuses on comparing different types of indicators, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category, as it deals with the organization, retrieval, and dissemination of digital information, including bibliometric data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely, as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of information from large datasets, including bibliometric data. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible, as they both involve the analysis and comparison of different constructs or algorithms. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possibility, as it deals with the analysis and modeling of social networks, which can include bibliometric data.
